title: Chelsea Clinton shares photo of CBP agents checking documents of passengers leaving domestic @Delta flight at JFK – twitchy.com
text:
Chelsea Clinton shares photo of CBP agents checking documents of passengers leaving domestic @Delta flight at JFK Posted at 1:59 pm on February 23, 2017 by Greg P. 
We’ve seen a couple of reports now that authorities asked for documents from passengers as they left Delta flight 1583 from San Francisco to New York’s JFK airport. From Vice video editor Anne Garret: My flight from SFO to JFK. We were told we couldn't disembark without showing our "documents." pic.twitter.com/9ugQspTqeX 
— Anne Garrett (@annediego) February 23, 2017 
Garret later identified the authorities as from CBP: 
— Anne Garrett (@annediego) February 23, 2017 
Here’s another report: These are customs agents forcibly checking the ID of every passenger deplaning from Delta flight 1583 tonight at JFK. A domestic flight. pic.twitter.com/fHMgyzCjo5 
— Britton Taylor (@brittontaylor) February 23, 2017 Trending 'Cool prank': Jonathan Allen spotted providing another reason why Hillary lost 
Chelsea Clinton used the photo to make a comment on America in 2017 even though she has absolutely no idea what’s going in the photo: America. 2017. Now we have to show IDs to board and get off? To gate agents then ICE officers? Just want to be clear (at least for today). https://t.co/QTxpFTNGlT 
— Chelsea Clinton (@ChelseaClinton) February 23, 2017 
Note the number of times her fact-free tweet has been shared. 
Other verified accounts are sharing the photos as well: 
— Jonathan Capehart (@CapehartJ) February 23, 2017 "Papers please."
